INSERT INTO `MovieReview` (`Movie_ID`, `Movie`, `Plot`, `Directors`, `Writers`, `Stars`, `Posters`) VALUES
(1,	'The Bad Guys 2',	'After their release from prison, The Bad Guys struggle to adjust to society but are inspired by Governor Diane Foxington (formerly the Crimson Paw) to prove they can be respected. Alongside Commissioner Misty Luggins, they investigate the new villain Phantom Bandit, initially suspecting Snake, only to learn he was with his girlfriend Susan (who is secretly part of the scheme). The group allies to expose the real culprit but gets framed for the crimes. They are captured by a trio of villainesses‚ÄîPigtail, Kitty, and Susan (aka Doom)‚Äîwho were using Susan to deceive them. Kitty, the true mastermind and former Crimson Paw, recruits them to steal the experimental Moon-X rocket to pull the world‚Äôs gold from the atmosphere using its magnets.\r\nDiane learns of Kitty‚Äôs plan from Professor Marmalade. The Bad Guys pretend to cooperate, secretly record Kitty‚Äôs confession, and steal Mr. Moon‚Äôs watch to sabotage the scheme. Kitty discovers the betrayal, exposes Diane‚Äôs past identity online, and calls the police on the Bad Guys. In the climax aboard the rocket, Diane boards despite being tranquilized, Luggins helps the Bad Guys escape to join the fight, and Pigtail and Doom turn against Kitty. Wolf tricks Kitty into crashing the rocket into a space station, foiling the gold heist. Diane stops Kitty from killing Wolf, they share a kiss and reconcile, and Luggins fakes their deaths to let them work undercover. Kitty escapes via pod, but she, Pigtail, and Doom are eventually arrested, while the Bad Guys earn a chance at redemption.',	'Pierre Perifel &bull; JP Sans',	'Yoni Brenner &bull; Etan Cohen &bull; Aaron Blabey',	'Sam Rockwell &bull; Marc Maron &bull; Awkwafina',	'movie0.jpg'),
(2,	'Kantara: A Legend - Chapter 1',	'Shva asks a villager how did his father disappeared in the jungle. The story goes many years back when an evil king ruled the village and treated people like slaves.He discovers a pouch from an old fisherman which has precious spices and leads to secret garden in the jungle the king falls prey to fisherman\'s plan and gets killed by the guardian.His son Rajshekar still a kid sees his fathers death in front of him but manages to escape and gets saved by tribal people of Kadapa.Rajshekar traumatized by his father\'s death swears never to enter the secret garden,he gets crowned as the king and gives birth to two kids Kulshekar and Kanakavathi.Meanwhile in Kantara village a young boy is found in a well and believed to be divine. He gets adopted by a tribal women who names him Berme.Years later Kulshekar gets crowned as king and is as ruthless as his grandfather he decides to cross the jungle boundary and enter secret garden where Berme and his men attack them. Berme with few of his men reaches Rajshekar\'s Bangara kingdom and discovers spices from forest are used for barter trade.Thou Berme and his men are kept as prisoners but Rajshekar releases them and Berme decides to cultivate the spices in his village and does barter system of the same in Bangara kingdom and gets romantically involved with Kanakavathi.When Berme enters secret garden to find more spices for trade he gets attacked by Kadapa tribal and finds that they share old grudge with his village. But Berme has no idea that he will be further be trapped into many unanswered questions and trap of betrayal.',	'Rishab Shetty',	'Rishab Shetty &bull; Anirudh Mahesh &bull; Shanil Guru',	'Rishab Shetty &bull; Rukmini Vasanth &bull; Jayaram',	'movie1.jpg'),
(3,	'Vidaamuyarchi',	'Arjun and Kayal, a Tamil couple married for twelve years and living in Baku, are heading toward divorce after Kayal\'s miscarriage, infertility, depression, growing emotional distance, and her affair with Prakash. Arjun, still heartbroken but dignified, agrees to the divorce and offers to drive her to her parents\' home in Tbilisi. During the road trip, their car is sabotaged at a filling station where Kayal had briefly befriended another Tamil couple, Deepika and Rakshith (who claim to be truckers). Kayal soon disappears after leaving with Rakshith supposedly to get help. Arjun uncovers the sabotage and learns from locals that she was likely kidnapped. He is later ambushed by Rakshith\'s criminal gang (including Deepika, Michael, and others), who reveal that Kayal supposedly hired them to murder Arjun for his money ‚Äî but they offer to kill her instead for a higher price. Arjun feigns agreement, fights his way out, and begins a desperate search to save her. In a violent climax, Arjun tracks down and eliminates most of the gang members. The gang had actually been kidnapping and trafficking women ‚Äî murdering their husbands and surgically altering the wives for resale. Kayal, their latest intended victim, is found alive in a hidden bunker and rescued. On the final drive to her parents\' house, Kayal asks why Arjun risked his life for her despite her betrayal. He simply answers, ‚ÄúBecause I still love you.‚Äù Moved by his unconditional devotion, they reconcile tearfully, choosing to rebuild their relationship.',	'Magizh Thirumeni',	'Magizh Thirumeni',	'Ajith Kumar &bull; Arjun Sarja &bull; Trisha Krishnan &bull; Regena Cassandrra',	'movie2.jpg'),
(4,	'Final Destination: Bloodlines',	'In 1968, Iris Campbell prevents the catastrophic collapse of the Skyview tower restaurant by acting on a premonition, saving everyone‚Äîincluding her fianc√© Paul‚Äîbut cheating Death\'s plan. Decades later, her granddaughter Stefani Reyes suffers nightmares of the disaster and discovers the truth from the dying, reclusive Iris: by averting the tragedy, Iris doomed the survivors and their descendants (who were never meant to exist) to die in the order they would have perished that night. Iris dies deliberately to prove it. Death then targets Iris\'s bloodline in sequence with elaborate accidents: uncle Howard (lawn mower), cousin Julia (garbage truck), Erik (MRI), Bobby (vending machine coil), and others. The family learns from mortician William Bludworth (a Skyview survivor) that Death can be cheated by killing someone else or dying and being revived. Revival attempts fail disastrously. Stefani, brother Charlie, and mother Darlene flee but crash; Darlene dies saving Charlie, who revives drowning Stefani. Believing they\'ve won, the siblings are killed shortly after by a derailing train and falling logs during prom preparations, sealing their fate.',	'Zach Lipovsky &bull; Adam B. Stein',	'Guy Busick &bull; Lori Evans Taylor &bull; Jon Watts',	'Kaitlyn Santa Juana &bull; Teo Briones &bull; Rya Kihlstedt',	'movie3.jpg'),
(5,	'Dragon',	'In 2014, diligent 12th-standard student Ragavan wins a gold medal in computer science but gets rejected by his crush Anjana for being too well-mannered. Heartbroken, he transforms into a rebellious \"Dragon\" at AGS Engineering College, accumulating 48 arrears, a mere 2% attendance, and a notorious ladies\' man reputation alongside friend Anbu. Suspended after a fight, he drops out, fakes having an IT job, and lives off friends and girlfriend Keerthi. When Keerthi dumps him for a better prospect (a professor earning ‚Çπ1.2 lakh/month), Dragon vows to earn more. He obtains a fake engineering degree by manipulating his father to sell land for ‚Çπ10 lakh, cheats through interviews, and lands a high-paying job at a US-based MNC (‚Çπ16 lakh/year). He rises quickly, gets promoted, transfers to the US, buys his parents a house and car, and gets engaged to Pallavi through family arrangement. However, Dean Mayilvahanan discovers the forgery and gives him an ultimatum: clear all 48 arrears in one attempt within 3 months with 100% attendance, or face exposure. Dragon returns to college secretly (lying about work and location), struggles but gets help from ex-girlfriend Keerthi (now a lecturer). He cheats again in the final exam by swapping answer sheets via the fake-degree agent, passes, and secures his job and wedding. On the wedding eve, guilt hits when he learns his cheated pass caused classmate Venkat to lose a Google job offer and attempt suicide. Dragon confesses everything‚Äîto his boss, dean, family‚Äîand surrenders to police, serving 6 months in jail. Venkat gets his job. After release, Dragon humbly works as a food delivery agent (‚Çπ25,000/month) while resuming genuine education. Impressed by his redemption, Mayilvahanan offers his daughter Harini in marriage, and Dragon accepts, beginning a new honest chapter.',	'Ashwath Marimuthu',	'Krishna Chepuri &bull; Ashwath Marimuthu &bull; Pradeep Ranganathan',	'Pradeep Ranganathan &bull; Anupama Parameswaran &bull; Kayadu Lohar',	'movie4.jpg'),
(6,	'Zootopia 2',	'Officers Judy Hopps and Nick Wilde are still fighting to be taken seriously as detectives - a struggle that gets worse when their off-the-books smuggling probe turns into a public disaster. With Chief Bogo threatening to split them up, the pair chase one last lead: a mysterious snake seen near the crime scene. That trail leads them to Gary DeSnake, a pit viper fugitive obsessed with exposing a secret behind the city\'s climate-controlling weather walls. When Judy and Nick realize he\'s telling the truth, they\'re suddenly framed by the powerful Lynxley family, whose buried crimes drove Zootopia\'s reptiles underground - and whose new plans are far more sinister. Branded fugitives, Judy and Nick join forces with eccentric beaver conspiracy buff Nibbles Maplestick to track down Gary and uncover the city\'s founding injustice - a case that will test their partnership, upend everything they thought they knew about Zootopia, and turn friends and enemies upside-down.',	'Jared Bush &bull; Byron Howard',	'Jared Bush',	'Ginnifer Goodwin &bull; Jason Bateman &bull; Ke Huy Quan',	'movie5.jpg'),
(7,	'F1: The Movie',	'Aging former F1 prodigy Sonny Hayes, sidelined 30 years earlier by a devastating crash at the Spanish Grand Prix, now lives nomadically as a racer-for-hire, battling gambling issues and failed marriages. After winning the 24 Hours of Daytona, his old teammate and friend Ruben Cervantes, owner of struggling backmarker team APXGP, recruits him as second driver alongside hotshot rookie Joshua Pearce to secure at least one Grand Prix win and save the team from sale by investors. Sonny joins the team in London, clashing with cocky Joshua and skeptical technical director Kate McKenna, while impressing others with his experience despite crashing in a test run. Early races (British, Hungarian) bring setbacks like poor pit stops and Sonny\'s rule-bending tactics (e.g., intentional crashes to trigger safety cars), but they score their first win in Hungary, earning Kate\'s respect as she builds a car suited to his aggressive style. Tensions rise: Joshua ignores Sonny\'s advice and crashes spectacularly in Italy; Sonny saves him from the burning wreck. They bond awkwardly via a tricked poker game, where Sonny lets Joshua win preferred status; Sonny and Kate begin a romance. Board member Peter Banning sabotages the team with false complaints about illegal upgrades, leading to FIA demands to remove them. Sonny crashes angrily in a subsequent race, gets hospitalized, and Ruben‚Äîlearning the full extent of Sonny\'s old injuries‚Äîdismisses him protectively. Sonny rejects Banning\'s offer to join a new team and stays loyal. In the season finale at Abu Dhabi, with upgrades cleared, Joshua pushes hard but crashes after a multi-car incident; Sonny, vision blurring from pain, sacrifices his lead to help Joshua but ultimately crosses the line first, clinching APXGP\'s victory and survival. Joshua declines a Mercedes offer to stay; Sonny retires from F1, shares a kiss and future promise with Kate, parts amicably with Joshua, and heads to Mexico for the Baja 1000‚Äînot for money, but pure love of racing.',	'Joseph Kosinski',	'Joseph Kosinski &bull; Ehren Kruger',	' Brad Pitt &bull; Damson Idris &bull; Javier Bardem',	'movie6.jpg'),
(8,	'Kaantha',	'Set in 1950s Madras, Kaantha is a period crime drama and murder mystery unfolding on the set of a film-within-a-film. Legendary but struggling director Ayya revives his shelved passion project Shaantha‚Äîa female-centric horror film inspired by his mother‚Äîthanks to studio backing that requires casting his former prot√©g√©, now superstar T. K. Mahadevan (loosely inspired by M. K. Thyagaraja Bhagavathar). Once mentor and mentee shared a father-son bond, but fame has corrupted Mahadevan into an ego-driven narcissist, leading to bitter clashes. Ayya introduces debutante heroine Kumari, a talented Burmese refugee actress who idolizes Ayya but falls for Mahadevan\'s charm (despite his marriage). Mahadevan hijacks the project‚Äîrenaming it Kaantha, altering the script and climax to suit his image‚Äîturning the set into a toxic battlefield of creative control, jealousy, and power plays. Kumari gets caught in the middle, her loyalty and love torn between the two men. Tensions explode when Kumari is shot dead on set with a real bullet during filming. The story shifts to a whodunit investigation amid suspects, motives, and shattered loyalties. The ego war between Ayya and Mahadevan ultimately costs an innocent life, leading to devastating guilt, reconciliation too late, and tragic consequences‚Äîincluding Ayya\'s suicide‚Äîhighlighting the corrupting influence of fame and pride in cinema.',	'Selvamani Selvaraj',	'Tamizh Prabha &bull; Sri Harsha Rameshwaram &bull; Selvamani Selvaraj',	'Dulquer Salmaan &bull; Bhagyashri Borse &bull; Samuthirakani',	'movie7.jpg'),
(9,	'The Amateur',	'Rami Malek stars as Charlie Heller, a brilliant but introverted CIA cryptographer and decoder working in a basement office at Langley. A quiet, socially awkward genius who restores old planes as a hobby, Charlie shares a loving marriage with his wife Sarah (Rachel Brosnahan). While she\'s away on a business trip to London, Charlie uncovers classified evidence that his superiors‚Äîincluding Deputy Director Alex Moore (Holt McCallany) and others‚Äîhave covered up politically motivated drone strikes by disguising them as suicide bombings. Tragedy strikes when Sarah is killed in a terrorist hostage attack in London. Devastated and enraged, Charlie demands the CIA pursue her killers, but his bosses refuse to act due to geopolitical complications. Using the incriminating files he possesses (and help from contacts like field agent Jackson \"The Bear\" O\'Brien (Jon Bernthal) and anonymous source Inquiline (Caitr√≠ona Balfe)), Charlie blackmails the agency into training him as a field operative. Assigned a ruthless mentor, Robert Henderson (Laurence Fishburne), Charlie embarks on a globe-trotting revenge mission to hunt down the terrorists responsible. He leverages his tech-savvy intellect‚Äîhacking, surveillance, and clever traps‚Äîrather than brute force, turning into an unlikely, methodical avenger. As he closes in on his targets, the CIA turns on him, viewing him as a rogue liability and attempting to eliminate him. The film blends gritty espionage, emotional grief (exploring Charlie\'s trauma and denial-to-acceptance journey), and high-stakes action in a familiar revenge-thriller framework. Charlie\'s unconventional style and moral dilemmas make him a compelling anti-hero in an otherwise formulaic story of personal vengeance against systemic indifference.',	'James Hawes',	'Robert Littell &bull; Ken Nolan &bull; Gary Spinelli',	'Rami Malek &bull; Rachel Brosnahan &bull; Jon Bernthal',	'movie8.jpg'),
(10,	'Thug Life',	'The story begins in 1994 with a violent gang shootout and police encounter in Old Delhi. Sakthivel and his brother Manickam rescue a young orphaned boy named Amaran amid the chaos and raise him as their own. Years later, Sakthivel has built a formidable empire (involving real estate and crime). However, an assassination attempt on his life shatters the trust within his \"family,\" leading him to suspect betrayal from those closest to him‚Äîincluding Amaran, whom he raised like a son, and possibly his brother. This sparks a intense conflict filled with themes of loyalty, suspicion, revenge, power struggles, and redemption as Sakthivel navigates betrayals in the criminal world while confronting his past. The narrative explores the heavy burden of a gangster\'s life, blending high-stakes action, drama, and Mani Ratnam\'s signature stylistic visuals. The film received mixed reviews‚Äîpraised for performances (especially Haasan and Silambarasan), cinematography, and production values, but often criticized for a predictable or generic plot in the second half compared to Nayakan. It\'s a solid underworld saga but didn\'t fully live up to the massive hype of the legends\' collaboration.',	'Mani Ratnam',	'Kamal Haasan &bull; Mani Ratnam',	' Kamal Haasan &bull; Silambarasan TR &bull; Trisha Krishnan',	'movie9.jpg'),
(11,	'Coolie',	'Simon runs a gold, luxury watches, and human organ (heart) trafficking operation at Visakhapatnam harbour with his lieutenant Dayal. Simon\'s son Arjun becomes a customs officer and rejects the family business.\r\nIn Chennai, strict boarding-house owner Deva (real name Dilip, ex-Kerala Police constable) investigates the suspicious death of his friend Rajasekhar, who was forced by Simon to modify an electric cremation chair for disposing of murder victims. Rajasekhar\'s daughter Preethi knows how to operate it and becomes a target. Deva rescues Preethi, infiltrates the gang, and discovers Dayal is an undercover cop (later revealed as Deva\'s former partner). Twists unfold: Kalyani (posing as Arjun\'s lover) is actually Dayal\'s undercover wife/partner. Dayal kills Arjun in revenge. Simon kills Kalyani. Deva storms Simon\'s ship, reveals his 30-year-old past as a coolie union leader who killed Simon\'s father Xavier during a revolt in Mandwa, and finally kills Simon. The coolies destroy the ship. A global syndicate leader Dahaa (son of Xavier\'s old partner Kakkar) kidnaps Deva, Preethi, her sisters, and others, offering Deva a position. Deva accepts to save his coolies. Dayal is buried alive. Preethi and her sisters leave abroad, forgiving Deva (unaware he is her biological father) and calling him \"uncle.\"',	'Lokesh Kanagaraj',	'Chandhru Anbazhagan &bull; Lokesh Kanagaraj',	'Rajinikanth &bull; Nagarjuna Akkineni &bull; Soubin Shahir',	'movie10.jpg'),
(12,	'Hurry Up Tomorrow',	'An insomniac musician encounters a mysterious stranger, leading to a journey that challenges everything he knows about himself. Music superstar Abel Tesfaye spirals through depression, substance abuse, and career pressure after a breakup, resisting performances despite encouragement from his manager Lee and losing his voice onstage. Parallel to this, Anima, an emotionally unstable fan who burns down a house and ignores her mother, travels to Los Angeles to see him. After Abel abruptly leaves his concert, Anima sneaks backstage, meets him, and they spend a night together, bonding over his unfinished song ‚ÄúHurry Up Tomorrow,‚Äù which reflects his loneliness. When Abel prepares to leave, Anima accuses him of abandonment and knocks him unconscious, leading to a surreal nightmare rooted in childhood trauma. Abel awakens tied up by Anima, who claims she wants to force him to confront his toxic patterns; when Lee arrives to rescue him, Anima kills Lee and threatens to burn Abel alive unless he opens up. Abel finally disarms her by singing ‚ÄúHurry Up Tomorrow,‚Äù after which Anima sets the room on fire and leaves, and Abel escapes into a hallway that transforms into a concert backstage, where he stares at himself in the mirror.',	'Trey Edward Shults',	'Trey Edward Shults &bull; The Weeknd &bull; Reza Fahim',	'The Weeknd &bull; Jenna Ortega &bull; Barry Keoghan',	'movie11.jpg'),
(13,	'Mickey 17',	'In 2050, debt-ridden Mickey Barnes flees a loan shark by joining a spaceship to colonize the ice planet Niflheim as an \"Expendable\"‚Äîa disposable worker who dies on dangerous missions (testing toxins, scouting), then gets \"reprinted\" as a new clone with memories intact. He dies 16 times en route and bonds romantically with security officer Nasha. On Niflheim, after Mickey 17 survives a fall into a crevasse (rescued by native creatures called \"Creepers\" instead of killed), a premature Mickey 18 is printed. Leader Kenneth Marshall bans \"Multiples\" (duplicates must die). The two Mickeys secretly share duties to avoid execution. Betrayals unfold: friend Timo abandons him and sells fuel as drugs; chaos erupts at a ceremony when baby Creepers emerge from a rock, one killed, one (Zoco) captured. The clones are exposed and arrested. Creepers demand Zoco back. Marshall plans genocide against them and destroys Mickey\'s backups. In a forced hunt (with bomb vests), Mickey 17 negotiates peace; Mickey 18 sacrifices himself by detonating to kill Marshall, satisfying the Creepers\' demand for retribution. Mickey 17 brokers coexistence between humans and sentient Creepers. Nasha leads the colony, bans the Expendable program, and the cloning machine is destroyed‚Äîending Mickey\'s disposability for good. A sharp, satirical take on exploitation, identity, colonialism, and greed through cloning absurdity and dark humor.',	'Bong Joon Ho',	'Bong Joon Ho &bull; Edward Ashton',	'Robert Pattinson &bull; Steven Yeun &bull; Michael Monroe',	'movie12.jpg'),
(14,	'Kingston',	'In the coastal hamlet of Thoovathur, Thoothukudi district, fishing is banned due to a rumored curse: the sea is haunted, and anyone who ventures out never returns, devastating the fishing community\'s livelihood.\r\nKingston (\"King\"), a local fisherman, works as the handyman for smuggler kingpin Thomas, believing he\'s transporting sea cucumbers. When he discovers the cargo is actually drugs, he rebels and sets out alone into the forbidden \"cursed\" sea to prove the myth false and catch fish to restore hope. He takes Thomas and his men hostage on the boat to expose the truth. They encounter horrors: skeletal remains in the water, then a foggy zone with zombie-like undead. Kingston aims to retrieve and bury Bose\'s coffin on an island to break the curse. Thomas escapes, captures Kingston, and reveals the truth: Bose was innocent; Thomas\'s grandfather smuggled gold long ago. Thomas killed his grandfather for the gold but never found it. The coffin actually contains Kingston\'s grandfather Solomon\'s body. Thomas threatens Solomon\'s ghost to spare him or he\'ll kill Kingston, but the ghost kills Thomas instead. Solomon\'s ghost urges Kingston to take the hidden gold and abandon his friends, but Kingston chooses loyalty over wealth. He escapes with the coffin and his friends, buries Solomon\'s body properly onshore‚Äîlifting the curse, restoring fish to the sea, and allowing the community to resume fishing. A sea-fantasy adventure blending horror, smuggling intrigue, family secrets, and redemption.',	'Kamal Prakash',	'Kamal Prakash &bull; Dhivek S Sekar',	'G.V. Prakash Kumar &bull; Divya Bharathi &bull; Azhagam Perumal',	'movie13.jpg'),
(15,	'Padakkalam',	'Four engineering students‚ÄîJithin, Ramzad, Nakul, and Kannan‚Äîat Shri Kartika Thirunal College discover supernatural chaos when charismatic professor Renjith uses an ancient artifact (a cursed dice/board game) to manipulate rival professor Shaji into a public fight, sabotaging Shaji\'s bid for Head of Department (HoD) and securing the post for himself. Jithin accidentally witnesses Renjith\'s powers while searching for a lost love note (taken by Shaji), and the friends research the artifact: it allows control or possession by applying an opponent\'s blood to the dice. They steal it to stop Renjith, but he retaliates by possessing Jithin (using leftover blood on a die), tormenting him and ruining his life/studies. To break the possession, they must complete the game with a special lock (in Renjith\'s possession). Attempts to 3D-print a duplicate fail; they ally with Shaji. A chaotic interruption causes a three-way body swap: Jithin in Shaji\'s body, Shaji in Renjith\'s, Renjith in Jithin\'s. Renjith (in Jithin\'s body) blackmails and causes trouble; Shaji (in Renjith\'s body) initially enjoys the perks but faces complications (including Shobha\'s pregnancy revelation to \"Shaji\"). Leverage comes from alcohol affecting swapped bodies. Renjith (with a fatal low RBC condition) refuses to swap back. In the final confrontation, Shaji subdues Renjith with alcohol; Jithin completes the game, restoring bodies. Shaji (in Renjith\'s body) sacrifices by jumping from a window to stop Renjith permanently. Jithin parts amicably with girlfriend Jeevika, Shaji reconciles with pregnant wife Shobha, and the students destroy the artifact, returning to normal life. Post-credits: Renjith goes missing from the hospital, hinting at more trouble. A campus-set supernatural comedy blending body-swap hijinks, possession, ancient magic, and college antics with humor and mild thrills.',	'Manu Swaraj',	' Nithin C Babu &bull; Manu Swaraj',	' Suraj Venjaramoodu &bull; Sharafudheen &bull; Sandeep Pradeep',	'movie14.jpg');
INSERT INTO `MovieReview_Comment` (`Comment_ID`, `AuthorName`, `Comments`, `Movie`) VALUES
(1,	'SiddharthS-43',	'<b>Fantastic Fantasy Thriller. Must watch</b><br />\r\nOne of the best fantasy-based thrillers to come out of Indian cinema-refreshingly unique and a new kind of storytelling that stands out in the genre. It\'s a complete entertainer for families and kids alike. A movie like this has arrived after a long time, and it\'s a delightful watch for all age groups. You walk out of the theatre excited, your mind buzzing with the story, eager to discuss the twists, the world-building, and the sheer creativity. It\'s the kind of movie that stays with you well after the credits roll.\r\nRated 10/10 - A magical ride worth every minute!',	'Padakkalam'),
(2,	'bruhbs',	'<b>Too late</b><br />\r\nVisuals : Overall good visuals but they were quite fascinating in some scenes. No scenes were foggy or too crowded, both lightning and camera work were good.\r\nSongs : except for the bgm in the last scene, songs (both bgms and sang songs) were just below average throughout the entire movie.\r\nPlot : Solid plot which could\'ve been presented in a much better way. Feels like it tried to be too complex, at the cost of lacking clarity. Plot twists seemed too redundant, the plot was constructing itself around a story only to getting ripped apart a few moments later. The spectator is caught up in a flux of continuous contradictory informations.\r\nI feel like if the plot had focused on a few key points, if it had set a clear context at the beginning and an epic/adventurous theme throughout the movie, it would\'ve been way more enjoyable.\r\nTLDR ; too complex for its own good, the movie is only watchable once. Really smooth visuals though.',	'Kingston'),
(3,	'manchuprasath',	'<b>A unique try!</b><br />\r\nWow! I never expected this film to be so interesting.\r\nCompletely new try. But wow. Engaging till the end.\r\nThe director deserves a huge applause. It never looked like his debut.\r\nBut the main strength is the cast. Everyone was good but Sharaf U Deen and Sandeep Pradeep were superb. Their cross acts were interesting.\r\nMusic and cinematography are good. Neatly edited to 2hrs running time.\r\nThe film was hilarious throughout. No lags at all. Just laughs and engaging screenplay. A different story made to a fun watch.\r\nOverall a good film that deserves more appreciation. A must watch for its unusual way.',	'Padakkalam'),
(4,	'ABOOBECKARA',	'<b>Double Good üíØ</b><br />\r\nCINEMATIC MASTERPIECE! A period drama set in 1950\'s Madras tinsel town ( there is a shot of LIC building on Mount Road under construction) , when big studios ruled. First half is the deadly ego clash between a veteran director Ayya (Samuthirakani) taking on the superstar KT Mahadevan (DQ) \'Nadippin Chakravarthy\' whom he discovered & mentored. Second half is pure Hitchcockian style murder mystery- who pulled the trigger? The way director has seamlessly blended both the parts together is what keeps you hooked till the end. What a solid performance by Dulquer Salmaan, his best till date, you can see the emotions of the character he plays in the breakdown \'mirror scene\'. And Samuthirakani as the ego driven maniac is perfect foil to DQ. Bhagyashri Borse is riveting and does a neat job as the girl torn between her loyalty to Ayya and her love for KTM. For Rana it is a cakewalk as comical investigation officer. Antony\'s editing and Jakes Bejoy bgm enhance the production. Yes it has pacing issues but is definitely one of the best films of the year, and is sure to sweep the awards.',	'Kaantha'),
(5,	'CallumJenningsHupko',	'This Sequel is actually really kinda good! (SHORT REVIEW?)\r\nI just got done watching The Bad Guys 2 the sequel to the 2022 The Bad Guys i watched the premiere movie of this and... honestly this sequel is actually really good!\r\nEven know it\'s have its flaws, but seeing the bad guys returning is really happy to me and the bad girls are really good in this.',	'The Bad Guys 2'),
(6,	'thamizhvanan-0',	'<b>Dulquer\'s Magic in Kaantha</b><br />\r\nDulquer Salmaan is absolutely perfect for his role in Kaantha. His performance carries the entire film with style and intensity. Every casting choice in this movie is spot-on - each actor fits their character beautifully and delivers strong performances. After a long time, we\'ve got a Tamil film that feels fresh, engaging, and emotionally powerful. Overall, Kaantha is a very good movie and definitely worth watching.',	'Kaantha'),
(7,	'tellingsreehari',	'<b>Appreciate the Effort, but...</b><br />\r\nPadakkalam is a unique enough experiment in a rather unused genre like supernatural fantasy comedy. The movie starts well and sets up the plot convincingly, but I do have issues with how the characters arrive at understanding the nuances. Well, let\'s give the makers some leeway for trying something different, and take it in the spirit of entertainment.\r\nIn spite of the decent start, it gets horribly confusing midway. At least to me it did. I know the swap-acting is super clever and all, but if you leave the crowd confused in the middle of an important scene, it defeats the purpose.\r\nSandeep Pradeep did a really good job, as did Sharaf U Dheen, who actually felt like he was breaking away from his usual style. I did not like Suraj in this one though. His performance felt off-key for the overall tone of the film.\r\nAll in all, it\'s a bold attempt to turn this thought into a film. But it drags and struggles for ideas toward the middle and the end. Once they got into it, the premise felt underused. The story had so much potential. It lacked intelligence, craft, and the screenplay was dull. Still, for what it tries to show, it did bring something new to the table.',	'Padakkalam'),
(8,	'rizaroselin',	'Cheating becomes normal thing to india cinema\r\nI have no idea how this movie received such a high rating. All of the performances are excellent. But Why has cheating become commonplace in Indian cinema these days? This film ...This kind of celebration cannot make us renowned.extremely annoying He cheats on other women and has a wife. The idea of a \"potray cheating girl\" is a fantastic one, however it is really frustrating.',	'Kaantha'),
(9,	'Robwinz',	'Better, Bolder, and Fartier\r\nA pretty solid sequel compared to the first, which I only found okay. The animation is top-notch, the story is familiar but still a blast, and I loved the fun nods to Mission: Impossible, Lethal Weapon, and even Silence of the Lambs?!? And yes-the fart jokes actually hit!\r\nDefinitely recommended!',	'The Bad Guys 2'),
(10,	'ShankZ09',	'<b>A Masterclass in Misleading Audiences</b><br />\r\nAs a true horror/fantasy fan, Kingston is a prime example of how NOT to make a film in this genre. The trailer built immense hype, promising a gripping supernatural experience. I even pre-booked the first show, expecting an engaging horror-fantasy spectacle.\r\nHowever, what I got was a run-of-the-mill drama disguised as something it\'s not. Beyond what was shown in the trailer, there\'s no real horror or fantasy element-just the same mediocre storytelling we\'ve seen countless times. The genre label feels like pure clickbait, designed only to lure audiences into watching a film that has nothing new to offer.\r\nA complete disappointment. If you\'re looking for genuine horror or fantasy, Kingston is a waste of time.',	'Kingston'),
(11,	'mrtow',	'It\'s good to watch something not boring\r\nThese days that everything comes out is obvious this one was such a refreshing and enjoyable experience from start to finish. The pacing was smooth, the action scenes were exciting, and the characters were fun to follow throughout the story. It didn\'t feel repetitive like many sequels often do instead, it brought a new energy that kept things engaging. Overall, it was a great watch that managed to be both entertaining and memorable.',	'The Bad Guys 2'),
(12,	'JagadishA-4',	'<b>It\'s a great movie.</b><br>Must watch movie\r\nJust now i watch movie in Inox with my friends. But movie is unbelievable. It\'s a experience. Each and every seen is important. Never watched movie like this in my life. I am a Hollywood movies fan. But today I am stunned. I want to see it again. What\'s a detailing. What a story. Beautiful camera work. Direction is ossom. Action secvences are stunning. What a Graphic work. Eding and BGM is mind blowing. Block buster movie.',	'Kantara: A Legend - Chapter 1'),
(13,	'EdithA-75',	'The Bad Guys 2 is a great work of animation art.\r\nThe Bad Guys 2 was one of the best animated films I\'ve ever seen. It has absolutely everything you\'d expect from an animated film and even exceeded my expectations. From the first film that came out in 2022, I knew that this wasn\'t the end of Bad Guys. I was sure that this incredible animation would continue, and it did. I congratulate the directors and their entire team for their excellent performance. I hope the THIRD installment becomes a REALITY and continues to surprise us.',	'The Bad Guys 2'),
(14,	'4753spnnie',	'<b>Brutal, Fresh, and a Lot of Fun!</b><br />\r\nReally enjoyed this one! It\'s super brutal again, but the story was told differently this time with the whole Bloodlines twist, which made it feel fresh and exciting. The plot was good and kept me entertained all the way through, with lots of intense moments, great pacing, and a few cool surprises along the way. I watched it in D-Box with Dolby Atmos - the sound was absolutely amazing, super powerful, and the moving seats made it even more intense and fun. Definitely a unique cinema experience. If you enjoy brutal action, great sound, and a fresh twist, you should totally check it out. Solid 7/10!',	'Final Destination: Bloodlines'),
(15,	'birupaneniakhil',	'A Devine BlockBuster filim the elevations at peaks\r\nKantara chapter 1 first half with full of comedy i have never seen in history filims the intervel scene will are mad overall first half is very good and when come to 2nd half from starting to ending the theaters will change into Temples Peak of elevations with God Overall movie is Devotional Blockbuster i have never seen this much of elevations in indian filim industry in recent times\r\nMy Honest Rating 9.7/10.',	'Kantara: A Legend - Chapter 1'),
(16,	'MatamM-8',	'Blockbuster. No one can imagine. It\'s an a great experience.\r\nI watched this movie today. I am stunned. It\'s not a movie. It\'s like Ramayana and Mahabharata. It\'s a Bhakthi saga. It\'s a must watch movie. It\'s a Masterpiece. Now Bollywood industry is in trouble. Till I didn\'t watch like this movie in Hollywood also. It\'s 100 times best than it\'s 1st sequel. South Indian film industry means Indian film industry is rocking. We are proud about you Director Vrishab Shetty. Thak you Vijay Kirangadoor Sir(Hombale Films). And also thank you to Vrishab Shetty and Team for your Hard work. Each and every frame is unbelievable.',	'Kantara: A Legend - Chapter 1'),
(17,	'alibrahim1',	'FUN! Loved the movie.. and from what I noticed in the movie theatre and from my friends. Everyone enjoyed it! I personally enjoyed the overall story.. The opening scene in the tower is amazing really. Showed the story back in the old days and after many years in our time how death (a person) follows everyone.\r\nI liked it.. Especially how the story carries on.. as a family curse plot. Some people find Final Destination movies repetitive.. true. I guess hardcore fans might expect/anticipate every single shot because it follows the same path as the old movies. But this one is very enjoyable.\r\nReally keeps you at the edge of your seat. Most accidents were amusing to be honest. Especially the one in the MRI machine. Very creative.',	'Final Destination: Bloodlines'),
(18,	'Ravennshadow Reel',	'<b>R.I.P. Tony Todd</b><br>\r\nIt was solid at least until the end then it got terrible\r\nThe start of the movie was fantastic best of all so far. After that story started unraveling in a solid way but as it progressed it became worse and worse and more in line with previous parts. Just unrealistic and dumb. Especially after they reached hospital. I mean if you know you are gonna die and only way to survive is to stop your heart and simulate death, you would do it quickly instead of giving death time to orchestrate everything.\r\nAlso, the mother in the end dies and her son does nothing even though he saw that it\'s gonna fall seconds ago.\r\nAnd finally the last moments they are running away from the train instead going towards the side.\r\nToo many stupid scenes that just ruined a good thing.',	'Final Destination: Bloodlines'),
(19,	'wileybeanstar',	'<b>A Visual Cinematic Journey</b><br /> As a Weeknd fan for so long this was such an amazing movie for his new album! It was such an amazing promo of his last album as \"The Weeknd\" and kinda like an amazing send off! Abel really did amazing with this and the music, Barry and Jenna also killed it with their roles too! It really was like a cinematic experience because it had like so much stuff packed into one, like a mushroom high lol! It was filled with like thriller, horror, mystery, music, a little action maybe and so much genres packed into a movie! I really enjoyed this and I suggest anyone who likes The Weeknd and music to watch this right now in theaters!',	'Hurry Up Tomorrow'),
(20,	'paulclaassen',	'<b>This amateur is a professional.</b><br />\r\nWe\'ve been bombarded with vengeance movies lately. I enjoy a good vengeance movie, providing the revenge is justified and exacted only on those who deserve it (therefore definitely NOT any of the John Wick movies with its kill counts well into the hundreds!)\r\nIn \'The Amateur\', Rami Malek stars as Charlie Heller, who works in Decryption Analysis for the CIA. When his wife Sarah is killed in a terrorist attack in London and the CIA refuses to intervene, Charlie takes matters into his own hands. Being the genius puzzle solver he is, Charlie utilizes surveillance cameras and advanced technology to identify the four terrorists.\r\nCharlie discovers his Director, Alex Moore, to be a rogue agent, and blackmails him to give him special CIA training. Trained by Col. Robert Henderson, Charlie soon realizes he would never be able to kill someone at gunpoint. Instead, he decides to use his knowledge to his advantage. But now, Moore and Henderson are on his trail to eliminate \'loose ends\'.\r\nCharlie meets Inquiline, whose husband worked for the KGB, but was killed. She continues to provide information to the CIA under a code name. They team up to bring the terrorists to justice. Unlike many cliched movies, this does not develop into a romance, which I found refreshing and more realistic.\r\nThe film dishes up a lot of information and it is so exciting that there\'s hardly time to blink! A Good script and solid performances elevates \'The Amateur\' above so many other vengeance movies. I did find some of his measures maybe a bit too extreme, but in general this is a believable and thoroughly entertaining action thriller.',	'The Amateur'),
(21,	'carlanastase',	'<b>Outstanding. Haunting. The Testimony of A Legend Alive</b><br />\r\nDiscovered Abel back in 2010, at the very beginning of his path, cluelessly, thanks to a guy from Arizona. And since he\'s remained a reference, he was the voice of my inner persona, my mind unveiled. Watching THIS Abel being set free has made my soul shiver; this testimony is an eulogy to God, a praise for the salvation, a release for each burden he carried all along - addiction, self-lying, heartbreaks, denial, pain, abandonment. I cried like a baby, curled up in my seat. I saw him growing, I saw him losing himself, I saw him getting back to life. He once said in his songs, \"I started too young to give up\". I feel like I reached a final√© with him at once. He matured his conscience, his conscience saved him. \"Hurry Up Tomorrow,\" is a whole manifesto. My heart clenched inside, tears were flowing down my cheeks. No doubt Jenna was his \"wake up call\" personified, the very moment you face yourself, you tear the mirror into pieces and kill the demons that obstructed your life for 15 years or more. Abel Tesfaye wrote history for almost two decades. Now he played NO CHARACTER and that\'s why he was immaculate. I saw a kid that cried for help, I saw humility, I saw the grace of the Lord upon him. Building idols is a sin. But recognizing the \"game changers\" is allowed. The Weeknd made a difference throughout his career, he struggled to reach balance and there he is - matured, redeemed, lucid and saved.Took him a \"weeknd\" to leave a deep mark behind. Haunting. For an old XO like me, this is haunting.',	'Hurry Up Tomorrow'),
(22,	'woodashe',	'<b>Not Enough Time to tell the story</b><br>\r\nI thoroughly enjoyed my time at the cinema watching The Amateur. It should have been a short series maybe 4-6 Episodes as opposed to a feature film. I think 2 hours did not leave enough time for proper character development. For example the lead speaks about his great friend played by Lawerence Fisburn in a scene at the end of the film. We never really saw how the two developed that bond as there are barely 2-3 scenes with them together throughout the movie. It was fun though and I feel more so because I watched it at the Theatre. Will definitely give it a rewatch once I can on my couch and recommend anyone who just wants to kick back to give it a watch.',	'The Amateur'),
(23,	'stephenmsaunders',	'<b>Killer nerd alert</b><br />\r\nAnd a new franchise is born. Falling somewhere between Jason, Bourne and James Bond, with a dash of the tech guy from Mission impossible, Remi Malik\'s The Amateur is a wonderfully entertaining and intelligent thriller, with extraordinarily strong supporting acts from just about everybody else involved, including an excellent Lawrence Fishburne, really on form here in a part which gives him real substance for once.\r\nIn a year, which has seen its fair share of lack Gloucester movies, this is a real crowd, pleaser, and no doubt we do well in box office as well as on home screen screens. Malik is exceptional believable, and as usual, evoking real emotion.',	'The Amateur'),
(24,	'curious-31675',	'Can\'t believe I watched the whole thing\r\nPainfully slow. This has no action and about as many thrills as a walk around Walmart. Well acted but that cannot save this. Made me sleepy. Way too much back story for this kind of seemingly old fashioned spy movie. The twists are too in frequent and there is no tension. If you saw the trailer you saw the parts worth watching.',	'The Amateur'),
(25,	'viKram',	'<b>Don\'t understand the hate</b><br />\r\n\"Hurry Up Tomorrow\" is everything its haters will never be: bold, uncomfortable, unforgettable. The Weeknd didn\'t make a film to be liked - he made one to expose how dull and predictable the industry (and its fans) have become. The people whining about it are the same ones who want every movie to feel like a Marvel trailer. This wasn\'t for you. It was for people who actually want art - not algorithm-tested mediocrity. Stay mad. While you cry on Twitter, Abel\'s out here bending cinema to his will.\r\nIt\'s raw, it\'s chaotic, it\'s deliberate. If you \"didn\'t get it,\" that\'s because it wasn\'t made for NPCs.',	'Hurry Up Tomorrow'),
(26,	'krishna-29850',	'<b>Super ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê</b><br>\r\nThe story, acting, screenplay and direction is all top notch. You\'ll run through a mix of emotions while watching this movie. The movie is emotional, delivers a good message and has blend of humour at the same time. The best 2.5 hours that I could spend on a Sunday afternoon. Actor Pradeep has done a commendable job and I believe it is a must watch.\r\nThe movie revolves around a man who abandons his education and then moves on secure a high paying job by unethical means. His life takes a turn when he is at the risk of getting exposed.\r\nThe movie delivers a message that no matter how many mistakes you have done in life, if you can own upto them you can still achieve whatever you want.',	'Dragon'),
(27,	'hariharanhh-86118',	'<b>No words man. No words.</b><br />\r\nI didn\'t expect this from the goated combo at all. Why just why did they have to disappoint us to this extent. Ts so bad that I who had never shared a review had to vent it out right now coz it made me doubt my life\'s purpose and question my existence while watching this. Seriously... Never putting my trust and never getting my hopes up for any other movies anymore.\r\nBruh just retire ffs. Have you guys not hoarded enough? Just give way for new gen talents. That would be the biggest help Kamal and Mani saar could do to the betterment of tamil cinema. Consider it rude or whatever but I don\'t care. I\'m too fed up. This is absolutely garbage.',	'Thug Life'),
(28,	'RajuKamal',	'<b>I wouldn\'t even give this movie a single star if that were possible.</b><br /> I sacrificed my sleep to watch the night show, and it ended up being a huge disappointment and a complete nightmare. While I\'ll admit the actors delivered good performances and the theatre\'s sound system was perfectly fine, the story was the real letdown. The movie was promoted as a gangster film, but there was absolutely nothing in it that resembled one. There was no strong plot, no gripping scenes, and no depth to the characters. It felt like a slow, directionless journey that left me bored and frustrated. Definitely not worth the hype or the time.',	'Thug Life'),
(29,	'kermitt-0',	'<b>This changed my life.</b><br />\r\nI usually never cry to movies but this one made me cry. This movie is not for everyone it\'s for people who can relate with abel this film was made for people like him who have done bad things and it\'s time to realize that its time to face every sin and this movie explains that but in a hard way but once you understand thus film you\'ll see how beautiful it is how life changing it is the message is clear no one\'s perfect but just because no one\'s perfect is not an excuse for doing Nad things. This movie is an absolute masterpiece if your going through stuff watch this movie trust me you won\'t regret it.',	'Hurry Up Tomorrow'),
(30,	'kk',	'NO real story, it seems like the movie industry has a lot of money to spend on useless movies like this!\r\nI don‚Äôt want to waste my time writing a review of this C**P.',	'Thug Life'),
(31,	'bfactor',	'<b>Intriguing premise, underwhelming movie</b><br />\r\nBong Jongho\'s next wide-screen project since his historic win at the Oscar\'s is rather a big let-down.\r\nFor such an intriguing premise, we should have been promised a story with colorful development and of gray morality, and yet were presented with such an obviously black-and-white good-triumphing-over-evil Hollywood movie.\r\nThe morality of science? The definition of one\'s self? The Ship of Theseus paradox? Like, such a wasted opportunity to explore the multitude of questions. I guess it\'s my fault to expect too much.\r\nRobert Pattinson and Toni Collette are amazing, though. Brilliant camera work and visual effects.',	'Mickey 17'),
(32,	'Guruprasad-7',	'Watched in OTT, having big stars wont make movie better .\r\nVery bad experience, not a content driven story instead its a action driven story, probably director first thought which big figures needed for this film and later he wrote a story to join there characters, so that it can bag more money, sad to see modern days movies not focussing on what sort of message needs to delivered for audience, what morals need to be followed in society',	'Coolie'),
(33,	'shivacharank',	'Ultimate movie acting super Pradeep and VJ Sidhu super performance totally movie fantastic and college stories with Anupama love story after the break up Pradeep will change lifestyle and become in IT company manager and movie after Pradeep will return come back collage and one more thing in college story one guy I don\'t no name but in movie the guy name kutty dragon he super comedy acting and Pradeep in college in last bench he was in phone he was talking with engage girl he with phone and after return come back ex girlfriend and last scene Pradeep, I will see again this movie with my friends.',	'Dragon'),
(34,	'mdalfin-10252',	'<b>Class and elegant</b><br />\r\nNext level movie for Tamil cinema such a great work from the team and Ajith Kumar. Amazing storytelling without any unnecessary elements movie goes well with realistic content and good cinematography along with bgm. All the cast characters are well connected with the character and significant role for villain holds the movie. The intermission and climax of the movie was outstanding. Thi is completely a standard and Hollywood style movie from Tamil industry a big applause to the pull a such a wonderful making and cinematography and fighting scenes. Ajith and Trisha chemistry works well and we connect with movie easily thanks to the director.',	'Vidaamuyarchi'),
(35,	'haydenfilen',	'<b>Super Unique</b><br />\r\nI love movies that step out of the comfort zone and aren\'t afraid to tell a weird, uncomfortable story. This movie is exactly that. Although it\'s not perfect, it\'s dark, comedic, thought-provoking & corny (in good and some bad ways lol). Robert Pattinson\'s character is a little annoying with the whole voice thing at first but his acting is incredible in this movie, props to him. Joon-ho had a super high bar to reach after Parasite, and this movie definitely reached that for me. His work is diverse, unique and poetic while being entertaining for all. Overall it is definitely worth a watch and one of my faves in recent years.',	'Mickey 17'),
(36,	'AlbaB-40',	'Karma and Career\r\nBest movie, Boys must watch this. You will find about your real goal Funny, emotional, drama all in together If i can give 100 stars i would definitely give that .You will enjoy the movie very very much One of the best movie i have ever seen in my life Thank you for providing this movie Really means a lot to me Thanks.',	'Dragon'),
(37,	'imdbfan-1011497867',	'<b>Copy Right logo of the Movie From Dragon Ball Z</b><br>\r\nI recently watched a movie that left me more frustrated than entertained. The most glaring issue was the blatant copy of the logo from the beloved Dragon Ball Z anime. This level of unoriginality set the tone for what would be an overall disappointing experience.\r\nFrom the start, it was clear that the filmmakers were more focused on cashing in on popular elements rather than delivering a unique or compelling story. The plot was predictable, the characters lacked depth, and the dialogue felt forced and cringeworthy. Even the action sequences, which could have been a saving grace, were poorly choreographed and did little to elevate the movie.\r\nWhat\'s even more frustrating is the audacity to rip off an iconic logo without any effort to hide it. This not only shows a lack of creativity but also a disrespect for the original creators and the audience. Fans of Dragon Ball Z will undoubtedly find this move both insulting and disappointing.\r\nIn conclusion, this movie is a prime example of how not to do production. A lack of originality, weak storytelling, and the shameless copying of a beloved anime\'s logo make it hard to recommend. Save your time and watch something else.',	'Dragon'),
(38,	'prajinjanaky',	'<b>Awesome Cinematography</b><br />\r\nThe movie is a fireüî• Everyone like this stuff Amazing performance by Ajith, trisha, arav, arjun, regina,etc..üëèüèª I want to rewatch again Anirudh rocked as before in the previous movies.\r\nNo age limit to understand Thala rocked the screen after 2 years and it is the greatest of all time comebacküíï.\r\nThala thala thala We are crazy to see you on good bad uglyüï∫üèª.\r\nWorth to watch for 1000rs on first day first show Run time is perfect Direction is too good I want a little mass to my idol Ajith Kumar.\r\nThe potrait of the movie is too good in ajith\'s perspectiveüíïüï∫üèªüî• I will rate 10/10 not as a fan and as a cinema loverüíï',	'Vidaamuyarchi'),
(39,	'BlipRangan',	'<b>superb stretch of Animation</b><br>\r\nThis movie looks like similar flops in GVP list but this movie have some more interesting story.\r\nPositive points, Story was nice and more interesting in way of created, acting is also good, location was also new and good. They tried Hollywood range of Ghost VFX which was also nice\r\nNegative points, The story was nice but needs more development and detailing to make more interesting, but have more logic mistakes, and the final main ghost was not shown well just simply in a human form. They tried to make out Hollywood style of jump scene location but that was not justified there with acceptable story. Even though it was a fantasy movie still much logic was missing. And more concepts in the story was pending not completed.',	'Kingston'),
(40,	'mateioanamaria',	'<b>It has it all. Don\'t trust haters, just watch it!</b><br />\r\nI just walked out of cinema and I want to give to you my honest review while it\'s still fresh in my head.\r\nThis movie is a gem, really something else. An anti-capitalist satire, mocking Trump in the most rightfully ways, sublime but point on. Dark humor and all, I giggled a lot throughout the movie. It reminded me of Idiocracy (hope it doesn\'t come true like Idiocracy did). So many characters and human typology, everyone is represented: from the rich to poor, from good guys to bad guys, from the smart to dumb,from emphatics to psychopaths etc. A perfect painting of a dysfunctional but ultimately beautiful society. The story is unusual and unpredictable and keeps you curious. Robert Pattinson delivers a complete role(s), I was impressed.\r\nAbsurd and fresh, it\'s a masterpiece! Go watch it , thank me later.\r\nP. S. Bong Joon-Ho- give this man an Oscar!',	'Mickey 17'),
(41,	'harishdgl-30982',	'<b>No AK comeback</b><br />\r\nAjith\'s on-screen presence is the main focus of this slow-paced, stylish flick!\r\nNot a single theater moment! Catastrophe.\r\nThe Worst Work Ani Has Done So Far!\r\nIt appears that Maghizh was compelled to produce this film, which is, in fact, a remake of Breakdown!\r\nIt could have been sped up, but the movie moves at such a slow pace that I can\'t stand the second half.\r\nArjun\'s role was a huge waste of time and had little scope.\r\nThe sole bright spot in the film is Dop, who keeps his attention on the frame.\r\nThe story could have been improved; several parts lacked logic. This is awful.\r\nI\'m hoping that if that continues in the vein of Vidamurachi, God will help Ajith. Let\'s wait until April 10.',	'Vidaamuyarchi'),
(42,	'illneverforgetu',	'Entertaining but underwhelming\r\nFun to watch- cute and some fun puns and clever lines.\r\nStill not as good as Bad Guys 2 (and yet very similar plot somehow üòÖ).\r\nCharacter development is eh- a plot itself is pretty predictable. No new or novel ideas in this one.\r\nBut cute enough for a fun family movie if you aren\'t expecting more :)',	'Zootopia 2'),
(43,	'AhsanA-05',	'<b>Worst 3 hours of my life</b><br />\r\nI had high hopes for Lokesh Kanagaraj with Coolie. After Leo fell short of expectations, I assumed he would learn from the missteps and deliver something stronger. Sadly, this turned out to be an even bigger disappointment.\r\nThe film is plagued with plot holes, nonexistent character development, and dull, predictable twists that fail to create any impact. To make matters worse, the budget spent on Pooja Hegde and Aamir Khan feels like a complete waste-two utterly useless characters who add nothing to the story.\r\nThe only saving grace here is Anirudh\'s music, which at least made the three hours somewhat tolerable. Without it, this film would have been unwatchable.',	'Coolie'),
(44,	'linneajenner',	'<b>Entertaining but forgettable</b><br />\r\nThe concept is cool and I really enjoyed certain bits of the film.\r\nThe charachters felt underdeveloped. Certain plot points either mysteriously vaporised or materialised unexpectedly.\r\nThere was a charachter that was clearly a commentary on Trump along with a selection of other social commentary points which are popular at the moment. Social commentary done right is subtle, social commentary done wrong breaks immersion and ruins escapism. Social commentary should preferably also not feel like it\'s all been done to death before. Although, I would probably be ok with it if it wasn\'t because Trump is constantly in the news and social media, when watching this movie I was looking for some escapism and a break from the world but instead lo and behold there was Trump again...\r\nI feel like this movie could have been so much more. It started out great but it\'s as if in order to give runtime to the cookie cutter social commentary it had to cut some of what could have made this movie great. Someone made a choice between entertainment value and trope like social commentary and this someone chose wrong. It\'s a shame, wasted potential for sure.',	'Mickey 17'),
(45,	'praveengm-77731',	'<b>Superr</b><br />\r\nGood and full enjoyment.is a mass entertainer powered by Rajinikanth\'s vintage swagger, Anirudh\'s thumping score, and a star-studded cast including Nagarjuna, Shruti Haasan, and Aamir Khan. While fans praise its style, action, and music, critics note uneven pacing and a weak second half. A treat for Rajini fans, though narrative depth takes a back seat.',	'Coolie'),
(46,	'volaji-1',	'Zootopia 2 (2025) returns to the animal metropolis with confidence, heart, and a slightly sharper edge.\r\nThe film smartly builds on the bond between Judy Hopps and Nick Wilde. Their dynamic feels more lived-in now, less about proving themselves and more about navigating trust, disagreement, and responsibility in a complex system. The humor is still snappy and family-friendly, but it\'s layered with wit that adults will appreciate-especially when the story pokes at bureaucracy, public perception, and how progress can stall or backslide.\r\nWhat Zootopia 2 does best is expand its themes without losing its soul. The film moves beyond simple prejudice and dives into subtler ideas: moral fatigue, social division, and the cost of always trying to \"do the right thing.\" These ideas are handled with Disney\'s trademark warmth, never preachy, but thoughtful enough to spark real conversations.',	'Zootopia 2'),
(47,	'onhisown127',	'Thin plot\r\nZootopia 2 is a much paler shade of the original. The plot is weak, and any heart the story has feel forced and syrupy. The actors from the original are paraded on for shallow one-off laughs, and most of the new characters are a snooze, especially the whole lynx family. The one shining new character is Mayor Brian Winddancer played by the always hilarious Patrick \"Kronk\" Warburton. Zootopia 2 sadly though is mostly one more example of how Disney hasn\'t and likely never will recover from the departure of John Lasseter.',	'Zootopia 2'),
(48,	'john_thyne',	'Disney rediscovers magic!\r\nWe loved this heartfelt film about righting past wrongs, sharing true feelings, and supporting others. The best part is that the filmmakers didn\'t lecture or use base shock to send those messages, they rediscovered the magic of Disney by using clean humor including many shared cultural references and amazing attention to detail. Truly entertaining for all this was an excellent movie.',	'Zootopia 2'),
(49,	'Sony Hayes',	'<b>Bad writing</b><br>\r\nThe score from Zimmer was good and some of the cinematography during the racing was impressive, particularly the scenes shot during live Grand Prix weekends.\r\nBut the writing and dialogue was laughable at best. The story is derivative and predictable. I nearly fell asleep twice. Parts honestly felt like it could have been written by a fourteen year old. The story arc was obvious and not innovative in the slightest.\r\nPitt keeps you engaged to a point, but even his star power isn\'t enough to elevate this script.\r\nUnless you are a big F1 fan I wouldn\'t recommend seeing this. I\'m sure it will do very well commercially.',	'F1: The Movie'),
(50,	'gypsee-44794',	'<b>Hollywood take on F1. Way off the mark</b><br>\r\nI really wanted to like this but unfortunately i nearly left a third of the way thru but thought I\'d stay just in case it changed. But no it was bad all the way through. From a F1 perspective totally unrealistic, it was more like a demolition derby movie with a cowboy at the helm. If your an American you would love this but a die hard fan that respects that F1 is an elite sport and has a mostly European background. Americans want what they don\'t have and when they get it they miss the whole concept of what it\'s about. They\'ve done it with the Grand Prix that they held turning them into trashy events. This movie is just a continuation of that! The only thing going for it was the cinematography and the fact that they had real snippets of races and drivers.',	'F1: The Movie'),
(51,	'Thabb0',	'<b>Absolutely worth it - especially in IMAX</b><br>\r\nLong movie, but it doesn\'t drag for a second. It\'s surprisingly gripping - keeps the tension up the whole time, and still manages to mix in a good amount of humor.\r\nBrad Pitt does a great job as Sonny Hayes. Fits the role perfectly.\r\nVisually and sound-wise, the film is a beast. In IMAX it\'s just incredible!\r\nYou feel the speed, the sound is massive, and the cinematography is top-notch. Music is pretty awesome too (IMAX!).\r\nThe story? Classic underdog vibes, a bit predictable at times - but honestly told in a way that works and really pulls you in.\r\nBottom line: I already see F1-Nerds complaining about realism - but who cares? It\'s a movie, and a damn fun one. If you\'re a hardcore fan, maybe just relax and enjoy the ride.\r\nIf you have the chance: IMAX is a no-brainer.',	'F1: The Movie'),
(52,	'Saif_smp',	'<b>Ride to the passion</b><br>\r\nF1 at its finest - speed, passion, and perfection. A must-watch for every motorsport fan. I really enjoyed the movie. I was there in the cockpit along with sunny.\r\nLiterally It made me cried with full of joy at the end of movie.\r\nThank you team for this extra ordinary work.\r\nExpecting more work like this.',	'F1: The Movie'),
(53,	'bobbymurala',	'<b>Dulquer Dulquer Dulquer</b><br/>\r\nAs always Dulquer has top notch acting, Samu and Bhagya did a great job too, first half is good reminds you of mahanati, second half where the movie becomes slow, I don\'t know why Rana did that character, slow paced, nothing like Dulquer other Telugu movies don\'t go with that expectation, all and all not for everyone.',	'Kaantha'),
(54,	'Kevin',	'<script>alert("hi bro");</script>',	'Final Destination: Bloodlines');